  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "In ganache, when a read occurs to an out of bounds array, it returns with an `error.message` of `Returned error: VM Exception while processing transaction: invalid opcode`\r\n\r\nFor example, when this test is run in isolation on ganache: https://github.com/Synthetixio/synthetix/blob/master/test/contracts/ExchangeRates.js#L941 it yields `Returned error: VM Exception while processing transaction: invalid opcode`\r\n\r\nWhen it is run on buidler.evm (via [this branch](https://github.com/Synthetixio/synthetix/tree/migrating-to-buidler)), it yields `Returned error: Transaction failed: revert`",
